 history of Palestine. Shedding new light on this foundational period, the authors explore not just major historical events and the development of an urban bourgeois lifestyle but a social field of vision of Palestinian life as exemplified in the Jerusalem community. Tracking the interplay between photographic images, the authors offer evidence of the unbroken field of material, historical, and collective experience from the living past to the living present of Arab Palestine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Israel & Palestine.2bisacsh1 aNassar, Issam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSheehi, Stephen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSheehi, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTamari, Salim, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTamari, Salim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishz978311099296008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022z9783110992939oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520382893zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382893zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382893/original  a978-3-11-07